         <ddi:abstract xml:lang="en">This research analysed the impacts of  resettlement projects on the livelihood of affected informal settlement dwellers in Kigali, the capital city of Rwanda. The resettlement projects considered are induced by both urban redevelopment projects and the disaster risk mitigation  relocation policy. The data were collected through interviews, focus group discussions and field observation.  Participants include key informants and  the heads of households in both selected resettlement sites and informal settlement communities that were waiting to be displaced.</ddi:abstract>
